==English==

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌmbəl|-ʌmbəl]]

===Verb===
'''mumble'''
#(transitive or intransitive) to [[speak]] [[unintelligibly]] or [[inaudibly]]; to fail to [[articulate]]
#:''Could you try not to '''mumble''' so I can hear you better?''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[mumista]], [[mutista]]
*Dutch: [[mompelen]]

===Noun===
'''mumble'''
#(countable) an [[quiet]] or [[unintelligible]] vocalization
#:''All I could hear was a '''mumble''' from the next room.''
#(countable) a [[low]] tone of [[voice]]
#:''He spoke in a '''mumble'''.

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[mumina]] (1)

